The South African Weather Service says that Gauteng residents can expect rain for the next seven days. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service says Gauteng residents can expect rain for the next seven days.However, no floods are expected in the low-lying areas of the province.Heavy rain is expected in Johannesburg, Pretoria and Vereeniging on Thursday.Forecaster Velentia Phakula says that residents should prepare themselves for a wet New Year s Day. Friday and Saturday into 1 January we are predicting 30% showers and thundershowers that are more likely in the afternoon. We are going to enter the new year on a wet note. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)